issue.title: "Less" op does not support int64 input type

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When running the GNMT onnx model, I see:
RuntimeError: [ONNXRuntimeError] : 9 : NOT_IMPLEMENTED : Could not find an implementation for the node Less(9)

ORT "Less" op does not support long input type.
ONNX spec for "Less" op has support for this: https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/master/docs/Operators.md#less

**Urgency**
GNMT onnx model should be executed out of the box.
https://github.com/NVIDIA/DeepLearningExamples/tree/master/PyTorch/Translation/GNMT

**To Reproduce**
This is the exported ONNX model:
https://drive.google.com/open?id=1cWYUg1V1FFgFo8dF-W0hR2tyezCzY_UV

This is the line in the model which causes this issue:
https://github.com/NVIDIA/DeepLearningExamples/blob/b728d42771e0861f7f90e963c3c80b9a44df62a5/PyTorch/Translation/GNMT/seq2seq/models/attention.py#L81

body: @RanACohen The onnx model you are trying to run in the Google Drive is created by me. This is the onnx model exported from a fork of GNMT model as a workaround. Now that 'int64' is supported for 'Less' op, you should be able to run the model with no issues. I exported the onnx model from GNMT master branch and uploaded it again (replaces the files). You can try running the new one. There's no need to use double for 'Less' op in this model. Sorry if the uploaded onnx model confused you.

@neginraoof Thanks a lot! Does not hurt to extend the runtime with Less(double) in any case  
I will use the updated one.
